\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. C. moschata} Duchesne ex Poiret, {\i Dict. Sci. Nat. }{\b 11}: 234 (1818). Like {\b 1} but leaves shallowly lobed or almost entire, softly hairy; peduncles of male flowers terete, of female flowers strongly expanded at top; calyx-lobes usually expanded and leaf-like at apex; fruit asymmetrical, curved, brown or reddish-yellow, with a musky odour.{\i  Cultivated as a vegetable in S. Europe.} ({\i Central America.})
\par

